Catherine Gentile is an American short story writer. She is a native of Hartford, Connecticut. She graduated from Saint Joseph College (Connecticut) with a Masters Degree. After a career in special education/mental health, she turned to writing. Her short fiction has been published in The Hurricane Review, The Ledge, The Long Story, and Kaleidoscope. She is a staff writer for Portland Trails.[1] She lives with her husband near Yarmouth, Maine, where she is completing her first novel, Sunday's Orphan.[2][3]
